-- ONGC to Spend $2 Billion Over Four Years to Sustain Output, Chronicle Says
-- B y   K e t a k i   G o k h a l e
-- 2010-12-29T03:09:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-29/ongc-to-spend-2-billion-over-four-years-to-sustain-output-chronicle-says.html
Oil & Natural Gas Corp. will spend
about $2 billion in the next four years to sustain output from
its onshore energy assets in western India, the Financial
Chronicle reported, citing Finance Director D.K. Sarraf.  To contact the reporter on this story:
